<br>
You got lucky for a long time.<br>
<br>
For whatever reason, be it pettyness, be it someone didn't like your attitude in some channel, be it you were using &quot;thier&quot; oven, the fuzz got called about your rulebreaking.<br>
<br>
Suck it up, and accept the fact that you finally got caught.<br>
<br>
Personally (and yes, I know this isn't anything remotely resembling the popular oppinion) they should never have let players pick thier own names.  They've proven time and time again that they can't handle the responcibilty.  Random Gen for everyone.<br>
<br>
As for consistancy, ya, it does suck.  But you know what?  Every speeder isn't caught by the cops.  Every fish isn't caught by the angler.  They do what they can with what they have.  And really, bothering you about your name takes what, 30 sec?  &quot;Hey you, bad name, *poof* pick a new one.  Next case!&quot;<br>
<br>
Now, whether they have enough to do all we would like them to do, thats another story (and most of us aggree they could use more CS staff).<br>
<br>
